&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Capacity planning&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="capacity-planning"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#capacity-planning" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Each stage needs its weights, activation buffers for in-flight microbatches, KV state for its layers, and communication workspace. The first and last stages may also own embeddings or vocabulary projection, so equal layer counts rarely mean equal memory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Benchmarking without fooling yourself&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="benchmarking-without-fooling-yourself"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#benchmarking-without-fooling-yourself" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plot stage utilization on a shared timeline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sweep microbatch count until gains flatten or memory rises sharply.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure first-result latency separately from steady throughput.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inject a deliberately slow stage to verify backpressure and queue bounds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;A production failure to design for&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="a-production-failure-to-design-for"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a href="#a-production-failure-to-design-for" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;One stage contains the final vocabulary projection and takes 35 percent longer than the others. Upstream activation queues grow until memory pressure causes retries. Rebalance using measured stage time and bound inter-stage buffers so imbalance fails visibly.&lt;/p&gt;
